class TextEditor {
public:
    TextEditor() : cursor(0), text("") {}

    void addText(string textToAdd) {
        text.insert(cursor, textToAdd);
        cursor += textToAdd.size();
    }

    int deleteText(int k) {
        int deleted = min(k, cursor);
        text.erase(cursor - deleted, deleted);
        cursor -= deleted;
        return deleted;
    }

    string cursorLeft(int k) {
        cursor = max(0, cursor - k);
        return getLastMin10Chars();
    }

    string cursorRight(int k) {
        cursor = min((int)text.size(), cursor + k);
        return getLastMin10Chars();
    }

private:
    string getLastMin10Chars() {
        int leftChars = cursor;
        int charsToReturn = min(10, leftChars);
        return text.substr(cursor - charsToReturn, charsToReturn);
    }

    int cursor;
    string text;
};
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: 
- addText: O(k)
- deleteText: O(k)
- cursorLeft: O(1)
- cursorRight: O(1)
space complexity: O(n)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The solution uses a string to store the text and an integer to keep track of the cursor position. The addText operation inserts the new text at the cursor position and updates the cursor. The deleteText operation removes characters to the left of the cursor and updates the cursor. The cursorLeft and cursorRight operations move the cursor and return the last min(10, len) characters to the left of the cursor. The getLastMin10Chars helper function is used to get the last min(10, len) characters.

